bug.short_desc: KDE Plasma File View desktop icons stay highlighted after mouse-over
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem:
I installed a clean system using image:
Fedora-KDE-Live-x86_64-25-1.3.iso
Moving the mouse over desktop icons highlighted them, and moving the mouse off removed the highlight.
Applied all maintenance to bring the system to current. Rebooted.
Now, when I mouse-over a desktop icon, it highlights. Moving the mouse off the icon does not remove the highlight. Moving the mouse of other icons highlights them as well. All icons remain highlighted, until the plasma-shell is restarted.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
plasma-workspace-5.8.6-3.fc25.x86_64
How reproducible:
Always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Install Fedora KDE spin 2. Apply maintenance 3. Reboot
Actual results:
Desktop icons stay highlighted as the mouse passes over them.
Expected results:
The highlight should be removed when the mouse is no longer over the icon.
Additional info:

Created attachment 1263057 Screenshot of multiple icons with stuck highlight
Also, tried downgrading plasma-workspace (and requisites) and rebooting; no change.
plasma-desktop-5.8.6-3.fc25 plasma-workspace-5.8.6-4.fc25 has been submitted as an update to Fedora 25. https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2017-d83ef1742d
Updated to plasma-workspace-5.8.6-4.fc25 (plus requisites) from updates-testing. No change.
(and you'll likely need to restart your session after update as well, if not obvious)
Updated plasma-desktop to 5.8.6-3 from updates-testing and the problem is resolved. Thanks!
plasma-desktop-5.8.6-3.fc25, plasma-workspace-5.8.6-4.fc25 has been pushed to the Fedora 25 stable repository. If problems still persist, please make note of it in this bug report.
